SEARCH
Package org.fluentjdbc

Class DbContextTableAlias

java.lang.Object
org.fluentjdbc.DbContextTableAlias
@CheckReturnValue public class DbContextTableAlias extends Object
Used to specify a table in a DbContextJoinedSelectBuilder joined SELECT statement. The same table can be joined several times by using different aliases. Example: 
 DbContextTableAlias perm = permissions.alias("perm");
 DbContextTableAlias m = memberships.alias("m");
 DbContextTableAlias p = persons.alias("p");
 DbContextTableAlias g = persons.alias("granter");

 perm.join(perm.column("membership_id"), m.column("id"))
         .join(m.column("person_id"), p.column("id"))
         .join(perm.column("granted_by"), g.column("id"))
         .list(....);
